The key insight in this solution is to express $\tan^2 20^\circ$ in terms of $\sin^2 20^\circ$ and $\cos^2 20^\circ$ using the identity $\tan^2 \theta = \frac{\sin^2 \theta}{\cos^2 \theta}$. This allows us to simplify the numerator and denominator of the expression.
Step 1: Express $\tan^2 20^\circ$ in terms of $\sin^2 20^\circ$ and $\cos^2 20^\circ$:
$$\begin{align*}
\frac{\tan^2 20^\circ - \sin^2 20^\circ}{\tan^2 20^\circ \sin^2 20^\circ} &= \frac{\frac{\sin^2 20^\circ}{\cos^2 20^\circ} - \sin^2 20^\circ}{\frac{\sin^2 20^\circ}{\cos^2 20^\circ} \cdot \sin^2 20^\circ}
\end{align*}$$

Step 2: Simplify the numerator and denominator:
$$\begin{align*}
\frac{\tan^2 20^\circ - \sin^2 20^\circ}{\tan^2 20^\circ \sin^2 20^\circ} &= \frac{\sin^2 20^\circ - \cos^2 20^\circ \sin^2 20^\circ}{\sin^4 20^\circ}
\end{align*}$$

Step 3: Use the identity $\sin^2 \theta + \cos^2 \theta = 1$ to simplify the numerator:
$$\begin{align*}
\frac{\tan^2 20^\circ - \sin^2 20^\circ}{\tan^2 20^\circ \sin^2 20^\circ} &= \frac{1 - \cos^2 20^\circ}{\sin^2 20^\circ}
\end{align*}$$

Step 4: The expression simplifies to 1.
The value of the expression $\frac{\tan^2 20^\circ - \sin^2 20^\circ}{\tan^2 20^\circ \sin^2 20^\circ}$ is $\boxed{1}$.
